   <h1>Re: [VB] Type 4 oil cooler mod</h1>
   <b>VeeWee111(-at-)aol.com</b><br/>
   <i>2002-04-11 15:55:08+00</i><br/>
   <br/>
   <pre>--part1_9.26487798.29e70bdc_boundary
Content-Type: text/plain; charset="US-ASCII"
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 7bit

In a message dated 4/10/2002 12:32:16 AM Pacific Daylight Time, 
tainlay(-at-)sbcglobal.net writes:
> Yes it was strange.  Berg might have made a mistake and sent the wrong tin 
> although I don't think so.  The way I think they wanted it to fit is that 
> their primary piece that is riveted on has ~1/4" extra on the top right and 
> front right (sides adjacent to the exhaust shell) that are tapered down on 
> the top and towards the shroud on the vertical edge.  The lip on the 
> exhaust shell has been bent in such a way that I think the idea is to let 
> it overlap the cooler cover while still fitting the stock exit duct.  
> Unfortunately this didn't work.

Hi Thomas,
That does not sound good.

> Skip forward to Sunday:  I found some tin at Kelley park and, having been
> immersed in the VW show atmosphere all day, became rejuvenated and vowed to
> get this done.  I remember the article in Hot VWs but not the exact details 
> and my copy is in storage.  However I did get some great insight from your 
> comments on the sheet metal mods as well as the pictures on P&C's site.  I 
> decided to try a different approach that would minimize the welding 
> required and used two of each piece to be modified.  For the sacrificial 
> piece I used tin that had some damage and for the Hoover bit I used one 
> that was broken.
> I found that the extension needed to be 7/8" so I just cut one piece in a 
> convenient location and the second piece with 7/8" more material.  With 
> that done I got them welded together today.  There was some warping but I 
> managed to get them to line up and only need to add the foam strips and it 
> will be done.
> 
> I noticed that you modified the exhaust shell in such a way that you could 
> still use the stock exit duct.  That's pretty cool.  I also like the 
> treatment to the shroud on the lower cooler feed side where it would meet 
> the Hoover bit (something the Berg tin doesn't address).  Can you tell me 
> why there's so much weld there?  Is that a repair in addition to the 
> extension or something else like reshaping the supply duct there?
> 
When you extend the tin wider you have to weld in new sealing surfaces.

> Another idea of yours that I used was the Hoover Bit reinforcement.  I used 
> 1/8" square stock cut to length and bent 90 degrees then welded to the 
> underside of the bit. I have attached some pics of my modified tin.  There 
> are a couple of additions I want to make like the treatment to the exhaust 
> shell in the corner where air could escape.  Anyway thanks for all your 
> help on this one!  Regards,  
> Thomas

Glad we could help!
Eric&Barb</pre>


